      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i'm not talking about changing the whole climate, just local resonance. like how a singer can break a glass with the right note? it's about finding the resonant frequency of the specific air mass or particle density in the cell. if i can just find the frequency that causes destructive interference with the pressure wave, wouldnt that create a localized effect? even if it's just a small pocket of stability. can you at least look at the math for wave interference and tell me if there's a theoretical hertz range that would work for a standard low-pressure oscillation?",
